WEBVTT

00:20.700 --> 00:26.480
Jane Eyre, by Charlotte Bronte We told by

00:26.480 --> 00:27.260
Florence Bell

00:45.380 --> 00:49.120
Chapter 1 My Story Begins

00:52.280 --> 00:57.660
In 1825, I was 10 years old. My

00:57.660 --> 01:01.440
father and mother were dead. I lived with

01:01.440 --> 01:04.620
my aunt and uncle, Mr. and Mrs. Reed.

01:05.860 --> 01:10.460
Their house was called Gateshead Hall. The house

01:10.460 --> 01:13.360
was in Yorkshire, in the north of England.

01:15.180 --> 01:18.120
My aunt and uncle, Reed, had two children.

01:19.080 --> 01:22.900
A boy, John, and a girl, Eliza.

01:24.520 --> 01:27.640
I liked my uncle, Reed, and he liked

01:27.640 --> 01:32.740
me. But in 1825, my uncle died.

01:34.500 --> 01:39.240
After that, I was very unhappy. My aunt

01:39.240 --> 01:42.360
Reed did not like me, and John and

01:42.360 --> 01:44.020
Eliza were unkind to me.

01:48.040 --> 01:50.680
It was a cold, rainy day in December.

01:51.860 --> 01:55.140
All of us were in the house. I

01:55.140 --> 01:55.980
wanted to be alone.

01:56.640 --> 02:00.660
I wanted to read. I opened a book.

02:01.720 --> 02:04.620
Then I heard my cousin John's voice.

02:05.520 --> 02:10.780
Jane, Jane Eyre, where are you? John shouted.

02:12.120 --> 02:14.700
He came into the room, and he saw me.
 
02:15.620 --> 02:19.200
Why are you reading my book? He asked.

02:19.940 --> 02:20.940
Give it to me.

02:21.860 --> 02:25.280
John took the book. He hit my head

02:25.280 --> 02:29.200
with it. I screamed. John hit me again.

02:30.140 --> 02:32.380
I pulled his hair, and I kicked him.

02:32.940 --> 02:35.080
Help! Help! Momoa!

02:35.620 --> 02:39.340
John shouted. Jane Eyre is hurting me.

02:40.240 --> 02:43.400
Aunt Reed ran into the room. She pulled

02:43.400 --> 02:44.560
me away from John.

02:45.180 --> 02:47.960
John hit me with a book, I said.

02:48.520 --> 02:51.520
I hate him, and I hate you too.

02:52.420 --> 02:55.860
You are a bad girl, Jane. My aunt

02:55.860 --> 02:57.980
said. Why do you hit me?

02:58.540 --> 03:02.740
You don't like me, I replied. John and

03:02.740 --> 03:04.520
Eliza are unkind to me.

03:04.520 --> 03:08.920
I want to leave Gateshead Hall. You want

03:08.920 --> 03:12.980
to leave? Aunt Reed said. Where will you go?
 
03:13.760 --> 03:16.920
Your parents are dead. You cannot live alone.

03:18.720 --> 03:23.220
Aunt Reed thought for a moment. My friend,

03:23.520 --> 03:27.760
Mr. Brocklehurst, is the owner of a school, she said.
 
03:28.280 --> 03:31.360
I will send you to Mr. Brocklehurst's school.

03:34.520 --> 03:37.920
A few days later, Mr. Brocklehurst came to

03:37.920 --> 03:38.680
Gateshead Hall.

03:39.820 --> 03:43.400
He was a very tall man. His eyes

03:43.400 --> 03:46.020
were dark, and his face was cruel.

03:47.380 --> 03:52.160
Jane Eyre, he said to me. God does

03:52.160 --> 03:58.440
not like bad children. God punishes bad children, Jane Eyre.
 
03:59.280 --> 04:03.580
God will punish John Reed, I replied. John

04:03.580 --> 04:06.040
Reed hits me, and he shouts at me.

04:07.320 --> 04:10.760
That is not true. You are a liar,

04:11.080 --> 04:13.860
Jane Eyre. Mr. Brocklehurst said.

04:14.400 --> 04:17.980
You must not tell lies, and you must

04:17.980 --> 04:19.680
not live here with your cousins.

04:20.460 --> 04:23.880
You will come to lowwood school. You will

04:23.880 --> 04:25.200
become a good girl.

04:25.910 --> 04:28.720
I want to come to your school, sir,

04:29.320 --> 04:32.140
I said. I want to leave this house.

04:33.600 --> 04:37.580
Bad girls are punished at my school, Jane

04:37.580 --> 04:40.180
Eyre. Mr. Brocklehurst said.

04:41.160 --> 04:43.880
The girls work very hard at lowwood.

04:45.180 --> 04:48.340
I will work hard. I will be a

04:48.340 --> 04:51.600
good pupil, Mr. Brocklehurst, I said.

04:53.040 --> 04:57.320
Two weeks later, I left Gateshead Hall. I

04:57.320 --> 04:58.520
went to lowwood school.

05:08.860 --> 05:09.820
Chapter 2

05:10.920 --> 05:11.900
Lowwood School

05:14.280 --> 05:17.880
It was the month of January. I arrived

05:17.880 --> 05:19.400
at lowwood school at night.

05:20.360 --> 05:23.180
A servant took me up some stairs and

05:23.180 --> 05:24.320
into a big bedroom.

05:25.860 --> 05:28.940
There were many beds in the room. The

05:28.940 --> 05:30.300
girls in the beds were asleep.

05:31.760 --> 05:33.760
The servant took me to an empty bed.

05:34.800 --> 05:37.940
I put on my night clothes, and I got into bed.
 
05:39.060 --> 05:41.440
Soon, I was asleep too.

05:44.060 --> 05:48.060
I woke up very early. A loud bell

05:48.060 --> 05:51.680
was ringing. The bedroom was dark and cold.

05:52.960 --> 05:56.020
I watched the other girls. They washed in

05:56.020 --> 05:58.320
cold water, and they dressed quickly.

05:59.880 --> 06:02.700
There was a plain brown dress next to

06:02.700 --> 06:06.440
my bed, and there was a pair of ugly, heavy shoes.
 
06:07.420 --> 06:11.420
I washed quickly. Then I put on my

06:11.420 --> 06:15.040
new clothes. I was very hungry.

06:16.120 --> 06:18.220
I followed the other girls down the stairs.

06:19.280 --> 06:21.920
We sat down at long tables in a

06:21.920 --> 06:23.060
large dining room.

06:24.140 --> 06:25.580
Our food was terrible.

06:26.800 --> 06:30.820
The food is bad again. One of the girls said.
 
06:30.820 --> 06:36.200
Stand up! A teacher shouted. Don't talk!

06:37.520 --> 06:42.200
We stood up. We did not speak. We

06:42.200 --> 06:45.300
walked into a big school room, and we sat down.
 
06:46.900 --> 06:49.300
There were about 80 girls in the school

06:49.300 --> 06:51.840
room, and there were four classes.

06:53.100 --> 06:55.820
The oldest girls were in the fourth class.

06:56.700 --> 06:58.460
I was in the first class.

07:00.160 --> 07:02.860
Four teachers came into the room, and we

07:02.860 --> 07:03.700
began our lessons.

07:05.020 --> 07:09.220
The lessons were not interesting. First, we read

07:09.220 --> 07:10.380
some pages in a book.

07:11.620 --> 07:15.080
Then, our teacher asked us questions about those pages.
 
07:16.680 --> 07:22.040
After four hours, we went outside. It was very cold.
 
07:23.300 --> 07:27.760
Very soon, a bell rang. Lessons started again.

07:33.020 --> 07:38.280
Three weeks passed. One afternoon, the head teacher

07:38.280 --> 07:39.520
came into the school room.

07:40.700 --> 07:44.600
The head teacher's name was Miss Temple. Mr.

07:44.880 --> 07:46.060
Brocklehurst was with her.

07:46.800 --> 07:51.140
We all stood up. I stood behind an older girl.
 
07:52.240 --> 07:54.760
I did not want Mr. Brocklehurst to see me.
 
07:56.140 --> 08:00.980
Mr. Brocklehurst walked slowly around the room. Everybody

08:00.980 --> 08:02.200
was very quiet.

08:03.440 --> 08:08.300
And then, I dropped my book. Mr. Brocklehurst

08:08.300 --> 08:09.180
stopped walking.

08:10.100 --> 08:14.100
He looked at me. Ah, the new girl,

08:14.960 --> 08:18.820
he said. Come here, Jane Eyre.

08:19.400 --> 08:22.740
Then, he pointed at two of the older girls.
  
08:23.780 --> 08:27.760
You two girls, put Jane Eyre on that

08:27.760 --> 08:30.120
high chair, he said.

08:31.160 --> 08:35.860
Look at Jane Eyre, everybody. Mr. Brocklehurst said,

08:35.860 --> 08:40.020
This child is bad. She is a liar.

08:40.700 --> 08:41.680
She will be punished.

08:42.540 --> 08:48.860
Miss Temple, teachers, girls, do not talk to this child.
 
08:50.460 --> 08:52.660
Then, he spoke to me again.

08:54.000 --> 08:57.180
Jane Eyre, you must stand on that chair

08:57.180 --> 08:59.600
for two hours, he said.

09:00.280 --> 09:01.920
You are a bad girl.

09:03.240 --> 09:08.600
That evening, I cried and cried. But Miss

09:08.600 --> 09:10.080
Temple was kind to me.

09:11.540 --> 09:14.660
You are a good pupil, Jane, she said.

09:15.460 --> 09:16.900
And you are not a bad girl.

09:17.740 --> 09:22.080
I am your friend, Jane. Thank you, Miss

09:22.080 --> 09:23.760
Temple, I said.

09:26.420 --> 09:30.420
Loward school was in an unhealthy place. The

09:30.420 --> 09:32.040
buildings were wet and cold.

09:33.380 --> 09:37.520
Mr. Brocklehurst owned the school. He was a rich man.
 
09:38.620 --> 09:40.740
But he did not buy warm clothes for

09:40.740 --> 09:43.980
us. And he did not buy good food for us.
 
09:45.040 --> 09:46.480
Everybody hated him.

09:48.100 --> 09:51.300
In the spring, many of the girls became

09:51.300 --> 09:54.160
sick. Some of them left the school.

09:55.220 --> 09:59.440
They never came back. Many of the girls died.
 
10:01.100 --> 10:05.420
That spring was a terrible time. We had no lessons.
 
10:06.780 --> 10:09.000
Miss Temple and the other teachers took care

10:09.000 --> 10:09.860
of the sick pupils.

10:11.420 --> 10:14.440
Mr. Brocklehurst had to buy better food for

10:14.440 --> 10:17.740
us. And he had to buy warm clothes for us.
 
10:18.880 --> 10:21.220
Mr. Brocklehurst never came to the school.

10:23.860 --> 10:27.000
The next year, Loward school moved to a

10:27.000 --> 10:29.980
better place. It was a healthier place.

10:31.100 --> 10:34.820
There were new school rooms, new bedrooms, and

10:34.820 --> 10:35.900
a new dining room.

10:36.820 --> 10:40.560
The new buildings were bright and clean. The

10:40.560 --> 10:41.540
teachers were happy.

10:42.500 --> 10:46.060
After that, I was happy at Loward school too.
 
10:47.700 --> 10:50.140
I was a pupil at Loward school for

10:50.140 --> 10:53.820
six years. Then, I became a teacher.

10:54.720 --> 10:56.820
I was a teacher at the school for

10:56.820 --> 11:00.980
two years. But I never returned to Gateshead Hall.
 
11:01.710 --> 11:04.180
And the reeds never wrote to me.

11:14.580 --> 11:17.920
Chapter 3. Thornfield Hall

11:20.870 --> 11:24.940
In 1833, I was 18 years old.

11:25.760 --> 11:29.560
In the summer, Miss Temple left Loward school.

11:30.460 --> 11:31.480
She got married.

11:32.560 --> 11:36.920
I wanted to leave Loward too. I wanted a new life.
 
11:38.100 --> 11:41.280
I will be a governess, I thought.

11:42.360 --> 11:45.600
I put an advertisement in a newspaper.

11:48.520 --> 11:51.820
October 1833, Loward

11:52.540 --> 11:56.320
A young woman wants to teach one or

11:56.320 --> 11:58.360
two children in their home.

11:59.740 --> 12:10.500
She teaches English, arithmetic, geography, religion, French, drawing and music, JE.
 
12:12.420 --> 12:16.560
I had a reply to my advertisement. The

12:16.560 --> 12:20.580
reply was from Mrs Fairfax of Thornfield Hall

12:20.580 --> 12:26.160
near Milcott. Milcott was about 70 miles from

12:26.160 --> 12:26.780
Loward school.

12:28.240 --> 12:31.200
Mrs Fairfax wanted a governess for a little girl.
 
12:32.980 --> 12:36.680
I wrote to Mrs Fairfax immediately. I was

12:36.680 --> 12:39.580
going to be a governess at Thornfield Hall.

12:41.260 --> 12:43.900
I traveled to Milcott in a coach.

12:44.880 --> 12:47.700
At Milcott, a servant met me.

12:47.700 --> 12:50.600
He took me to Thornfield Hall.

12:51.680 --> 12:55.340
At Thornfield Hall, another servant opened the door.

12:56.300 --> 12:59.500
She was smiling. She took me into a

12:59.500 --> 13:00.980
small, warm room.

13:01.920 --> 13:04.660
A lady was in the room. She was

13:04.660 --> 13:05.740
sitting by the fire.

13:07.620 --> 13:11.420
Are you Mrs Fairfax? I asked her.

13:12.500 --> 13:17.900
Yes, my dear. She said. And you are Miss Eyre.
 
13:18.400 --> 13:21.800
Are you cold? Sit by the fire, Miss

13:21.800 --> 13:24.680
Eyre. A servant will bring you some food.

13:26.320 --> 13:30.060
Mrs Fairfax is very kind. I said to

13:30.060 --> 13:32.760
myself, I will be happy here.

13:34.480 --> 13:38.280
Will I see Miss Fairfax tonight? I asked.

13:39.220 --> 13:43.080
Mrs Fairfax looked at me. She smiled.

13:44.340 --> 13:49.300
Miss Fairfax? No, no. She said.

13:50.300 --> 13:52.580
Your pupil's name is not Miss Fairfax.

13:53.500 --> 13:56.840
Your pupil is Adele Barone.

13:58.120 --> 14:02.040
Adele's mother was a French woman. Adele is

14:02.040 --> 14:05.300
Mr Rochester's ward. He takes care of her.

14:06.640 --> 14:11.900
Mr Rochester? Who is Mr Rochester? I asked.

14:13.360 --> 14:17.680
Mr Edward Rochester is the owner of Thornfield Hall.
 
14:18.720 --> 14:23.220
Mrs Fairfax said, I am his housekeeper. I

14:23.220 --> 14:24.920
take care of Thornfield Hall.

14:25.960 --> 14:29.820
Mr Rochester is not here now. He does

14:29.820 --> 14:31.040
not like this house.

14:31.940 --> 14:33.840
He is often away from home.

14:36.140 --> 14:40.160
I was very tired. Mrs Fairfax took me

14:40.160 --> 14:43.440
up the wide stairs. She took me to my room.
 
14:44.380 --> 14:48.320
I went to bed immediately and I slept well.
 
14:51.220 --> 14:56.180
The next morning I woke early. The sun was shining.
 
14:57.140 --> 15:00.860
I put on a plain black dress. I

15:00.860 --> 15:02.200
opened my bedroom door.

15:03.120 --> 15:06.920
I walked along a corridor and down the wide stairs.
 
15:07.860 --> 15:12.200
I walked out into the sunny garden. I

15:12.200 --> 15:15.400
turned and I looked up at my new home.
 
15:17.060 --> 15:19.940
Thornfield Hall was a beautiful house with many

15:19.940 --> 15:21.000
large windows.

15:21.800 --> 15:24.060
The garden was beautiful too.

15:26.860 --> 15:29.980
After a few minutes Mrs Fairfax came into

15:29.980 --> 15:32.280
the garden. She spoke to me.

15:33.580 --> 15:38.500
Good morning Miss Eyre. She said, you have woken early.
 
15:39.640 --> 15:43.920
Mr Del is here. After breakfast you must

15:43.920 --> 15:45.280
take her to the school room.

15:46.000 --> 15:47.600
She must begin her lessons.

15:49.240 --> 15:53.020
A pretty little girl walked towards me. She

15:53.020 --> 15:54.480
was about eight years old.

15:55.420 --> 15:57.800
She spoke to me in French and I

15:57.800 --> 15:58.780
replied in French.

16:00.660 --> 16:03.580
After breakfast I took Adele to the school

16:03.580 --> 16:06.100
room. We worked all morning.

16:07.200 --> 16:10.300
Adele enjoyed her lessons and I was happy.

16:12.340 --> 16:16.180
In the afternoon Mrs Fairfax took me into

16:16.180 --> 16:17.980
all the rooms of Thornfield Hall.

16:19.040 --> 16:21.340
We looked at the paintings and at the

16:21.340 --> 16:22.260
beautiful furniture.

16:23.440 --> 16:25.200
We walked along the corridors.

16:26.740 --> 16:30.940
Come up onto the roof Mrs Fairfax said.

16:31.600 --> 16:35.500
You will see the beautiful countryside around Thornfield Hall.
 
16:36.330 --> 16:41.520
We walked up many stairs. At last we

16:41.520 --> 16:42.780
were at the top of the house.

16:43.740 --> 16:45.560
We walked along the top corridor.

16:46.860 --> 16:50.360
Mrs Fairfax opened a small door and we

16:50.360 --> 16:51.320
walked onto the roof.

16:52.680 --> 16:57.380
Look Miss Eyre. Mrs Fairfax said, you can

16:57.380 --> 16:58.700
see for many miles.

17:00.000 --> 17:02.520
We stood on the roof for a few

17:02.520 --> 17:05.920
minutes. Then we went back into the house.

17:06.720 --> 17:10.600
We walked carefully towards the stairs. The top

17:10.600 --> 17:12.380
corridor was narrow and dark.

17:14.280 --> 17:17.000
Suddenly I heard a strange laugh.

17:18.440 --> 17:22.340
Who is that Mrs Fairfax? I asked.

17:23.540 --> 17:27.460
Mrs Fairfax did not reply. She knocked on a door.
 
17:28.300 --> 17:33.680
Grace, she said. The door opened. Behind the

17:33.680 --> 17:34.960
door was a small room.

17:35.620 --> 17:37.780
A servant was standing at the door.

17:38.620 --> 17:43.260
Be quiet Grace, please. Mrs Fairfax said.

17:44.320 --> 17:47.960
The woman looked at Mrs Fairfax. Then she

17:47.960 --> 17:48.800
closed the door.

17:49.800 --> 17:56.640
That was Grace Poole. Mrs Fairfax said. She works up here.
 
17:57.540 --> 18:00.980
Sometimes she laughs and talks with the other servants.
 
18:02.140 --> 18:07.120
Don't worry about Grace. Please come downstairs now,

18:07.420 --> 18:08.100
Miss Eyre.

18:17.460 --> 18:18.940
Chapter 4

18:20.200 --> 18:21.520
Mr Rochester

18:24.520 --> 18:28.600
Three months passed. I had not met the

18:28.600 --> 18:30.040
owner of Thornfield Hall.

18:31.000 --> 18:32.980
Mr Rochester had not come home.

18:34.620 --> 18:38.360
One January afternoon I went out and I

18:38.360 --> 18:39.520
walked towards the road.

18:40.640 --> 18:42.300
I was going to the village of Hay.

18:43.320 --> 18:45.600
I was going to post a letter in the village.
 
18:46.860 --> 18:51.480
Hay was two miles from Thornfield Hall. The

18:51.480 --> 18:53.760
day was fine but it was very cold.

18:54.980 --> 18:58.080
I walked quickly and soon I was near the village.
 
18:59.840 --> 19:03.440
Suddenly a big black and white dog ran past me.
 
19:04.180 --> 19:06.600
A moment later a man on a black

19:06.600 --> 19:07.840
horse followed the dog.

19:09.100 --> 19:13.020
Then I heard an angry shout. The dog

19:13.020 --> 19:16.140
ran past me again. It was barking loudly.

19:17.200 --> 19:21.040
I turned round. The horse had fallen on

19:21.040 --> 19:24.380
the icy ground and the man had fallen from the horse.
 
19:25.120 --> 19:27.240
I walked towards them.

19:28.320 --> 19:31.400
Can I help you sir? I asked.

19:32.300 --> 19:37.400
My horse fell. I've heard my foot. The man said.
 
19:38.540 --> 19:41.640
The horse stood up. The man tried to

19:41.640 --> 19:44.720
stand up too but he could not stand.

19:45.640 --> 19:47.220
He fell onto the ground again.

19:48.200 --> 19:53.240
The man was about 35 years old. He

19:53.240 --> 19:56.360
was not handsome but he had a strong face.
 
19:57.440 --> 20:01.420
He had dark eyes and black hair. He

20:01.420 --> 20:04.440
was not very tall but his body was powerful.
 
20:05.900 --> 20:10.580
I'll bring somebody from Thornfield Hall. I said.

20:11.780 --> 20:16.040
Do you live at Thornfield? The man asked.

20:17.120 --> 20:20.020
I am the governess. I replied.

20:21.440 --> 20:25.480
Ah yes. The governess. The man said.

20:26.340 --> 20:27.840
Help me please.

20:29.460 --> 20:32.440
The man stood up very slowly and he

20:32.440 --> 20:33.800
put his hand on my shoulder.

20:34.660 --> 20:38.740
He walked slowly towards his horse. I helped him.
 
20:38.740 --> 20:41.240
He pulled himself onto the horse.

20:42.620 --> 20:47.340
Thank you. Now go home quickly. The man said.
 
20:48.500 --> 20:49.300
And he rode away.

20:51.080 --> 20:54.780
I walked on to the village and I posted my letter.
 
20:56.120 --> 20:58.660
Then I returned to Thornfield Hall.

20:59.940 --> 21:02.320
Bright lights were shining in the big house.

21:03.140 --> 21:04.380
I went inside.

21:05.180 --> 21:08.760
A big black and white dog walked towards

21:08.760 --> 21:11.320
me. It came from the dining room.

21:12.140 --> 21:13.900
I had seen the dog before.

21:16.140 --> 21:19.420
Whose dog is that? I asked a servant.

21:20.560 --> 21:24.540
It's Mr. Rochester's dog. The servant replied.

21:25.620 --> 21:29.840
Mr. Rochester has come home but he has hurt his foot.
 
21:29.840 --> 21:32.660
His horse fell on some ice.

21:34.780 --> 21:39.800
I smiled. The owner of Thornfield Hall had returned.
 
21:41.260 --> 21:44.400
But I did not see Mr. Rochester again that day.
 
21:47.200 --> 21:50.940
I saw Mr. Rochester the next day. He

21:50.940 --> 21:52.220
sent for me in the evening.

21:53.220 --> 21:55.860
I put on a clean dress. I brushed

21:55.860 --> 21:57.120
my hair carefully.

21:58.960 --> 22:01.900
Mr. Rochester was in the large sitting room.

22:02.760 --> 22:04.380
He was sitting in a big chair.

22:05.420 --> 22:07.820
His right foot was on a small chair.

22:09.160 --> 22:11.960
Mrs. Fairfax and Adele were sitting with him.

22:13.460 --> 22:17.300
This is Miss Eyre, sir. Mrs. Fairfax said.

22:18.480 --> 22:22.340
Mr. Rochester looked at me. He did not smile.
 
22:24.440 --> 22:27.900
Sit by the fire, Miss Eyre, he said.

22:28.800 --> 22:30.340
Where have you come from?

22:31.680 --> 22:37.680
From Lowood School, I replied. I was there for eight years.
 
22:38.700 --> 22:44.120
Eight years? Mr. Rochester said. That is a long time.
 
22:45.060 --> 22:46.080
Who are your parents?

22:46.880 --> 22:51.820
I have no parents, sir. I answered. They are dead.
 
22:52.800 --> 22:57.440
But where is your home, Miss Eyre? Mr. Rochester asked.
 
22:58.180 --> 23:03.240
I have no home, sir. I have no family. I said.
 
23:04.620 --> 23:08.140
Why did you come to Thornfield Hall? Mr.

23:08.660 --> 23:09.140
Rochester asked.

23:09.920 --> 23:13.580
I wanted to leave Lowood, sir. I replied.

23:14.580 --> 23:16.720
I put an advertisement in a newspaper.

23:18.120 --> 23:20.180
Mrs. Fairfax replied to my advertisement.

23:21.720 --> 23:26.640
Yes, I did. Mrs. Fairfax said. Miss Eyre

23:26.640 --> 23:28.180
is a good teacher, Mr. Rochester.

23:29.900 --> 23:32.860
Mr. Rochester smiled for the first time.

23:33.680 --> 23:38.800
You are very young, Miss Eyre. He said.

23:39.980 --> 23:42.360
I am eighteen, sir. I replied.

23:44.120 --> 23:48.860
Mr. Rochester smiled again. He did not ask me more questions.
 
23:51.420 --> 23:54.540
After that evening, I did not see Mr.

23:54.840 --> 23:55.960
Rochester for a few days.

23:56.920 --> 24:00.280
Then, one night, he sent me again.

24:01.560 --> 24:06.320
Sit near me, Miss Eyre, he said. Mrs.

24:06.400 --> 24:08.180
Fairfax will talk to Adele.

24:09.460 --> 24:13.520
I sat down quietly, but I did not speak. 

24:13.620 --> 24:15.720
The fire was very bright.

24:16.580 --> 24:20.940
I saw Mr. Rochester's face clearly. I saw

24:20.940 --> 24:22.960
his large, dark eyes.

24:23.660 --> 24:27.000
He was smiling. He was happy.

24:28.540 --> 24:31.420
After a minute, Mr. Rochester spoke.

24:33.180 --> 24:35.500
Miss Eyre, he said.

24:36.740 --> 24:38.920
You are looking up to me very carefully.

24:40.480 --> 24:41.880
Am I a handsome man?

24:43.360 --> 24:45.660
No, sir, I said.

24:46.520 --> 24:50.960
You speak the truth, Miss Eyre. Mr. Rochester said.
  
24:52.060 --> 24:53.180
Look at me again.

24:54.480 --> 24:56.360
Am I a kind man?

24:57.740 --> 25:01.680
No, sir, I said again. You are smiling

25:01.680 --> 25:04.800
now, but you are not always kind.

25:06.320 --> 25:11.100
That is true, Mr. Rochester replied. I have

25:11.100 --> 25:12.140
had a difficult life.

25:12.980 --> 25:16.580
I have met bad people. I have been

25:16.580 --> 25:17.800
a bad person myself.

25:19.340 --> 25:24.700
Now, Thornfield Hall is my home. But I hate this house.
  
25:26.600 --> 25:31.120
You are very young, Miss Eyre. You cannot understand me.
 
25:32.460 --> 25:35.960
You are right. I don't understand you, sir.

25:36.800 --> 25:38.960
I said. I stood up.

25:40.160 --> 25:43.460
Where are you going? Mr. Rochester asked.

25:44.220 --> 25:48.600
It is late. A doll must go to bed. I said.
 
25:49.920 --> 25:54.180
Are you frightened of me, Miss Eyre? Mr.

25:54.320 --> 25:55.060
Rochester asked.

25:56.100 --> 26:01.320
No, sir, I replied. But you say strange things, sir.
 
26:02.880 --> 26:04.400
Mr. Rochester smiled.

26:05.940 --> 26:08.400
Take a doll to her bedroom now, Miss

26:08.400 --> 26:09.920
Eyre. He said.

26:09.920 --> 26:12.200
We will talk again tomorrow.

26:15.220 --> 26:18.800
After that night, we talked together many times.

26:19.820 --> 26:22.080
Mr. Rochester was an interesting man.

26:23.080 --> 26:28.540
But he was a strange man, too. I often thought about him.
 
26:30.120 --> 26:34.540
Why does Mr. Rochester hate Thornfield? I asked myself.
 
26:35.800 --> 26:39.620
Thornfield Hall is a beautiful place. But Mr.

26:39.940 --> 26:41.000
Rochester is not happy.

26:51.320 --> 26:52.280
Chapter 5

26:53.460 --> 26:54.080
Fire

26:56.540 --> 27:00.320
It was March. One night, I was in

27:00.320 --> 27:02.720
bed. But I was not asleep.

27:03.560 --> 27:08.940
The house was quiet. Suddenly, I heard a

27:08.940 --> 27:11.000
sound in the corridor outside my room.

27:12.460 --> 27:19.320
Who's there? I said. Nobody answered. Then, I

27:19.320 --> 27:20.480
heard a strange laugh.

27:22.100 --> 27:25.020
I got out of my bed, and I

27:25.020 --> 27:28.480
went quietly to the door. I listened.

27:28.480 --> 27:34.940
I heard another sound. Somebody was walking up

27:34.940 --> 27:36.580
the stairs to the top corridor.

27:38.460 --> 27:41.900
Then, I heard somebody close a door.

27:43.720 --> 27:47.460
Was that Grace Poole? I said to myself.

27:48.640 --> 27:50.940
Yes, it was Grace.

27:52.240 --> 27:56.060
Why was she laughing? And why is she

27:56.060 --> 27:57.500
walking in the house at night?

27:58.840 --> 28:03.020
Is she mad? I must tell Mrs. Fairfax

28:03.020 --> 28:06.580
about this. I will speak to her now.

28:09.040 --> 28:11.800
I put on some clothes, and I opened

28:11.800 --> 28:15.040
the door. There was a candle on the

28:15.040 --> 28:16.260
floor outside my room.

28:17.400 --> 28:21.380
The candle was burning. There was thick smoke

28:21.380 --> 28:22.040
in the corridor.

28:22.740 --> 28:26.920
I went into the corridor. I looked around

28:26.920 --> 28:31.440
me. The door of Mr. Rochester's bedroom was open.
 
28:32.320 --> 28:35.040
And the smoke was coming from Mr. Rochester's

28:35.040 --> 28:39.120
room. I ran into the room.

28:40.640 --> 28:42.200
Wake up, sir.

28:43.960 --> 28:45.880
What happened, Jane?

28:47.080 --> 28:51.400
There was a fire, sir. Grace Poole tried to kill you.
 
28:52.800 --> 28:57.440
Stay here, Jane. Open the window. I'll go upstairs.

29:00.240 --> 29:02.240
I sat in a chair by the window.

29:03.460 --> 29:08.060
Time passed. At last, Mr. Rochester returned.

29:09.540 --> 29:14.720
Please don't worry, Jane, he said. Grace Poole

29:14.720 --> 29:19.280
is a strange woman, but she won't hurt anybody tonight.
 
29:20.840 --> 29:25.720
I stood up. Good night, sir, I said.

29:27.200 --> 29:30.980
Mr. Rochester held my hand. He looked at

29:30.980 --> 29:32.660
me, and he smiled.

29:34.560 --> 29:40.600
Thank you. My dear friend, he said, you

29:40.600 --> 29:42.280
saved my life tonight, Jane.

29:44.100 --> 29:47.220
Good night, sir. I said again.

29:49.000 --> 29:52.160
I went back to my bed. I was

29:52.160 --> 29:56.760
very tired. But at first, I could not sleep.
 
29:58.300 --> 30:04.400
Suddenly, I understood something. I loved Mr. Rochester.

30:05.520 --> 30:09.620
He had smiled at me. He had held my hand.

30:11.020 --> 30:14.700
Did he love me? I did not know.

30:15.780 --> 30:20.200
But I thought about Mr. Rochester for a long time.
 
30:22.720 --> 30:25.540
I did not see Mr. Rochester the next

30:25.540 --> 30:28.440
day. He did not send for me.

30:29.960 --> 30:32.800
In the evening, I went down to Mrs.

30:33.120 --> 30:37.460
Fairfax's sitting room. The housekeeper was looking out of the window.
 
30:39.180 --> 30:42.980
The weather has been good today, Mrs. Fairfax

30:42.980 --> 30:47.040
said. Mr. Rochester had a good day for his journey.
 
30:48.040 --> 30:52.340
His journey. Where has he gone? I asked.

30:53.160 --> 30:54.160
I was surprised.

30:55.740 --> 30:59.540
He has gone to Ingram Park. Mrs. Fairfax

30:59.540 --> 31:03.960
replied. Mr. Rochester will stay there for a week or more.
 
31:04.940 --> 31:08.380
He has many friends. All his friends will

31:08.380 --> 31:09.980
be at Ingram Park this week.

31:11.820 --> 31:14.660
Will there be any ladies at Ingram Park?

31:15.520 --> 31:20.980
I asked. Yes, Mrs. Fairfax said. There will

31:20.980 --> 31:22.260
be many ladies there.

31:23.180 --> 31:27.120
Miss Blanche Ingram will be there. Mr. Rochester

31:27.120 --> 31:29.060
has known her for many years.

31:30.300 --> 31:35.480
Is Miss Ingram beautiful? I asked. She is

31:35.480 --> 31:38.460
very beautiful. Mrs. Fairfax said.

31:39.600 --> 31:45.980
Will Mr. Rochester marry her? I asked. Mrs. Fairfax smiled.
 
31:47.480 --> 31:52.440
I don't know Miss Eyre, she replied. I don't know.
 
31:54.560 --> 31:58.160
I was very unhappy. I went up to

31:58.160 --> 32:00.640
my bedroom. I looked in my mirror.

32:02.320 --> 32:07.080
Jane Eyre, I said to myself. You are

32:07.080 --> 32:11.000
not pretty. And you are poor. Mr. Rochester

32:11.000 --> 32:12.560
will never marry you.

32:13.420 --> 32:17.200
He will marry Miss Blanche Ingram. She is

32:17.200 --> 32:20.300
a rich lady. You are a poor governess.

32:21.160 --> 32:24.740
Forget Mr. Rochester Jane Eyre. Forget him.

32:34.620 --> 32:39.680
Chapter 6. Guests at Thornfield Hall.

32:42.060 --> 32:45.680
Two weeks later, a letter arrived for Mrs.

32:45.980 --> 32:50.480
Fairfax. Mr. Rochester will return on Thursday.

32:51.880 --> 32:55.040
Mrs. Fairfax said. Some of his friends will

32:55.040 --> 32:57.320
come here with him. There will be many

32:57.320 --> 32:59.060
guests at Thornfield Hall.

33:00.880 --> 33:06.800
On Thursday evening, Mrs. Fairfax, Adele and I were in Adele's bedroom.

33:08.080 --> 33:10.320
Mrs. Fairfax was looking out of the window.

33:11.920 --> 33:15.680
The guests are arriving now, Mrs. Fairfax said.

33:17.360 --> 33:22.480
I went to the window and I looked out. There were three carriages.

33:23.280 --> 33:29.360
Two people were riding horses. Mr. Rochester was riding his big black horse.

33:30.720 --> 33:33.520
A beautiful young woman was riding a white horse.

33:34.800 --> 33:37.120
Mrs. Fairfax pointed to the young woman.

33:38.640 --> 33:44.080
That is Miss Ingram, the housekeeper said. Then she went downstairs.

33:45.440 --> 33:47.600
Adele wanted to go downstairs too.

33:48.480 --> 33:54.320
No, Adele. I said, we cannot go downstairs tonight.

33:55.280 --> 33:57.600
Mr. Rochester is talking to his guests.

33:59.760 --> 34:03.280
The next day, Mrs. Fairfax came into the school room.

34:05.520 --> 34:09.520
Mr. Rochester wants you to meet his guests tonight, Miss Eyre.

34:10.240 --> 34:13.120
She said, Adele must meet them too.

34:13.440 --> 34:17.840
Later, Adele and I went quietly into the sitting room.

34:18.800 --> 34:22.240
And soon, eight ladies came into the room.

34:23.040 --> 34:26.640
One of them was tall, dark and very beautiful.

34:27.280 --> 34:29.520
She was Blanche Ingram.

34:30.480 --> 34:32.320
Adele ran towards her.

34:33.920 --> 34:36.720
Good evening, beautiful lady.

34:37.360 --> 34:38.960
She said in French,

34:39.440 --> 34:44.400
what a pretty little gal, Blanche Ingram said.

34:45.520 --> 34:52.080
Miss Ingram spoke to the other ladies and she spoke to Adele, but she did not speak to me.

34:54.560 --> 34:58.080
Half an hour later, the gentleman came into the room.

34:59.360 --> 35:04.880
I looked at Mr. Rochester. He saw me, but he did not speak to me.

35:05.520 --> 35:08.160
Ms. Ingram pointed at Adele.

35:09.200 --> 35:13.520
Why does not this little girl live at school, Mr. Rochester?

35:14.160 --> 35:15.200
She asked.

35:16.160 --> 35:18.400
Adele learns her lessons at home.

35:19.040 --> 35:22.400
Mr. Rochester replied, she has a governess.

35:23.600 --> 35:28.720
Oh, yes, that small woman by the window, Miss Ingram said.

35:29.680 --> 35:31.680
I had many governesses.

35:32.320 --> 35:33.680
I hated all of them.

35:33.680 --> 35:36.480
They were all ugly and stupid.

35:38.000 --> 35:42.800
Later, Miss Ingram and Mr. Rochester sang some songs together.

35:43.840 --> 35:45.840
Mr. Rochester had a fine voice.

35:47.040 --> 35:49.040
I listened to the songs.

35:49.760 --> 35:51.200
Then I left the room.

35:52.400 --> 35:54.080
Mr. Rochester followed me.

35:55.760 --> 35:57.360
What is wrong, Jane?

35:58.240 --> 35:59.280
He asked.

35:59.920 --> 36:01.280
Nothing is wrong, sir.

36:01.280 --> 36:03.680
Nothing is wrong, sir, I said.

36:04.640 --> 36:05.680
But I am tired.

36:06.720 --> 36:07.840
I am going to my room.

36:09.120 --> 36:10.000
Good night, sir.

36:12.000 --> 36:12.880
You are tired.

36:14.240 --> 36:18.320
And you are unhappy too, Mr. Rochester replied.

36:19.760 --> 36:21.280
There are tears in your eyes.

36:22.960 --> 36:24.400
Rest now, Jane.

36:26.000 --> 36:29.440
But please come and meet my guests tomorrow evening.

36:30.320 --> 36:31.520
Don't forget, my...

36:33.040 --> 36:34.480
Don't forget, Jane.

36:37.040 --> 36:40.160
The guests stayed at Thornfield Hall for two weeks.

36:41.600 --> 36:44.880
Every evening, I went to the sitting room with Adele.

36:46.080 --> 36:47.360
Nobody spoke to me.

36:48.480 --> 36:51.280
Mr. Rochester and Miss Ingram were always together.

36:53.200 --> 36:56.720
One afternoon, Mr. Rochester went to Milcott.

36:57.680 --> 36:59.520
He returned late in the evening.

37:00.560 --> 37:02.000
I met him at the front door.

37:03.840 --> 37:05.760
Another guest has arrived, sir.

37:06.560 --> 37:07.360
I told him.

37:08.240 --> 37:09.680
His name is Mr. Mason.

37:10.480 --> 37:12.240
He has come from the West Indies.

37:14.320 --> 37:17.280
Suddenly, Mr. Rochester's face was pale.

37:18.480 --> 37:20.240
He held my hand tightly.

37:21.840 --> 37:22.400
Mason.

37:23.680 --> 37:24.800
The West Indies.

37:25.760 --> 37:27.840
Mason, he said.

37:29.120 --> 37:30.240
Are you ill, sir?

37:31.040 --> 37:31.760
I asked.

37:33.360 --> 37:35.600
Jane, my little friend.

37:36.640 --> 37:38.880
I've had a shock, he said.

37:39.920 --> 37:42.000
Bring me a glass of wine, please.

37:43.840 --> 37:45.520
I went quickly to the dining room.

37:46.480 --> 37:48.160
I returned with a glass of wine,

37:48.880 --> 37:50.720
and I gave it to Mr. Rochester.

37:52.640 --> 37:54.320
What are my guests doing?

37:55.200 --> 37:55.840
He asked.

37:57.040 --> 37:58.880
They are eating and laughing, sir.

37:59.680 --> 38:00.400
I replied.

38:01.440 --> 38:03.840
Mr. Mason is talking to the other guests.

38:05.760 --> 38:08.640
One day, they will all hate me.

38:09.920 --> 38:11.040
Mr. Rochester said.

38:12.560 --> 38:14.320
Now go into the dining room again.

38:15.440 --> 38:17.600
Tell Mason to meet me in the library.

38:19.840 --> 38:21.520
I gave Mr. Mason the message.

38:22.720 --> 38:24.160
Then I went to my bedroom.

38:25.600 --> 38:26.720
I got into my bed.

38:28.400 --> 38:32.800
Later, I heard Mr. Rochester coming up the stairs with Mr. Mason.

38:34.160 --> 38:35.680
They were laughing and talking.

38:37.520 --> 38:39.520
Soon, I was asleep.

38:50.480 --> 38:51.360
Chapter 7

38:52.960 --> 38:54.240
A terrible night.

38:55.360 --> 38:57.840
Some hours later, I woke up.

38:58.880 --> 39:00.960
A terrible cry had woken me.

39:01.920 --> 39:03.120
The moon was bright.

39:03.920 --> 39:05.920
Its light was shining through my window.

39:06.960 --> 39:08.160
I listened.

39:09.120 --> 39:11.120
Then, I heard somebody shouting.

39:12.560 --> 39:13.520
Help!

39:13.520 --> 39:14.560
Help!

39:14.560 --> 39:15.520
Rochester!

39:15.520 --> 39:16.560
Help me!

39:18.000 --> 39:20.000
The voice came from the top corridor.

39:21.600 --> 39:22.400
Help!

39:22.400 --> 39:27.680
I got out of bed, and I put on a dress and some shoes.

39:27.680 --> 39:29.280
I opened my door.

39:29.280 --> 39:33.760
All the guests were in the corridor outside the bedrooms.

39:33.760 --> 39:36.160
They were all asking questions.

39:36.160 --> 39:37.600
What happened?

39:37.600 --> 39:38.800
They asked.

39:38.800 --> 39:40.000
Is there a fire?

39:40.000 --> 39:41.200
Who is hurt?

39:41.200 --> 39:43.200
Where is Mr. Rochester?

39:43.200 --> 39:45.200
I am here.

39:45.200 --> 39:47.200
Mr. Rochester said.

39:47.200 --> 39:51.200
Mr. Rochester, I am here.

39:51.200 --> 39:55.520
Mr. Rochester said he was walking down the stairs from the top corridor.

39:56.800 --> 39:58.640
What is wrong, Mr. Rochester?

39:59.440 --> 40:00.640
Ms. Ingram asked.

40:01.360 --> 40:02.320
What has happened?

40:03.840 --> 40:04.880
Nothing is wrong.

40:05.760 --> 40:07.120
Mr. Rochester replied.

40:08.160 --> 40:10.320
One of the servants has had a bad dream.

40:11.200 --> 40:12.080
Go back to bed.

40:13.920 --> 40:15.120
I went back to my room.

40:16.080 --> 40:17.360
But something was wrong.

40:18.560 --> 40:19.920
I did not get into my bed.

40:20.800 --> 40:21.440
I waited.

40:22.720 --> 40:25.040
Soon, somebody knocked on my door.

40:26.080 --> 40:27.040
I opened the door.

40:28.160 --> 40:30.400
Mr. Rochester was standing in the corridor.

40:31.840 --> 40:33.520
Jane, follow me.

40:34.480 --> 40:35.840
Do not make a sound.

40:36.800 --> 40:38.000
Mr. Rochester said.

40:39.600 --> 40:41.440
We went up to the top corridor.

40:42.560 --> 40:46.800
Mr. Rochester unlocked a door, and we went inside a room.

40:47.040 --> 40:50.480
Mr. Mason was sitting on a chair in the room.

40:50.480 --> 40:56.320
His face was pale, and his shirt was covered with blood.

40:56.320 --> 40:59.680
Then I heard a terrible laugh.

40:59.680 --> 41:02.160
The sound came from the next room.

41:03.600 --> 41:07.440
Grace Poole is a mad woman, I thought.

41:07.440 --> 41:10.640
Why does Mr. Rochester have a mad servant?

41:12.080 --> 41:15.840
Mr. Rochester spoke quietly to Mr. Mason.

41:17.600 --> 41:20.880
I am going to bring a doctor, Richard.

41:21.840 --> 41:22.320
He said.

41:23.440 --> 41:24.480
Then he spoke to me.

41:25.920 --> 41:27.120
Stay here, Jane.

41:28.080 --> 41:29.520
Wash Mr. Mason's arm.

41:30.560 --> 41:32.080
But do not speak to him.

41:34.400 --> 41:36.000
Mr. Rochester left the room.

41:36.960 --> 41:38.560
I washed Mr. Mason's arm.

41:40.000 --> 41:42.400
We waited for Mr. Rochester and the doctor.

41:43.600 --> 41:45.360
Mr. Mason did not speak to me.

41:46.240 --> 41:47.680
And I did not speak to him.

41:49.760 --> 41:52.720
After two hours, Mr. Rochester returned.

41:53.760 --> 41:54.960
The doctor was with him.

41:56.240 --> 41:58.400
The doctor looked at Mr. Mason's arm.

41:59.920 --> 42:02.480
She bit me, Mr. Mason said.

42:03.200 --> 42:04.080
I came up here.

42:04.720 --> 42:05.840
I wanted to see her.

42:06.480 --> 42:07.680
I wanted to help her.

42:08.400 --> 42:09.440
But she bit me.

42:11.040 --> 42:12.480
Me quiet now, Richard.

42:13.280 --> 42:15.280
Mr. Rochester said quickly.

42:16.800 --> 42:19.360
The doctor put a bandage on Mr. Mason's arm.

42:20.320 --> 42:22.480
Mr. Rochester put Mr. Mason's coat

42:22.480 --> 42:24.080
round the injured man's shoulders.

42:25.200 --> 42:27.040
Then he spoke to me again.

42:28.800 --> 42:30.080
Run downstairs, Jane.

42:31.040 --> 42:34.320
Unlock the small door at the side of the house, he said.

42:35.280 --> 42:36.240
We will follow you.

42:37.920 --> 42:40.960
I went quickly downstairs and I opened the door.

42:41.600 --> 42:45.360
Outside the door, a servant was waiting with the carriage.

42:46.560 --> 42:49.040
Mr. Mason and the doctor came out of the house.

42:50.160 --> 42:51.440
They got into the carriage.

42:52.720 --> 42:55.280
Then Mr. Rochester came out of the house too.

42:56.640 --> 42:59.680
Mr. Mason spoke to him through the window of the carriage.

43:01.440 --> 43:01.920
Help her.

43:03.040 --> 43:05.040
Be kind to her, Rochester.

43:06.080 --> 43:06.560
He said.

43:07.520 --> 43:10.800
Yes, I will, Mason.

43:11.760 --> 43:12.960
Mr. Rochester said.

43:14.400 --> 43:16.560
The servant drove the carriage away.

43:18.560 --> 43:20.800
Will you walk in the garden with me, Jane?

43:21.680 --> 43:22.960
Mr. Rochester asked.

43:24.000 --> 43:25.840
I do not want to sleep now.

43:27.280 --> 43:30.000
Yes, I will, sir, I said.

43:31.680 --> 43:33.360
Soon it was morning.

43:34.480 --> 43:36.000
The birds were beginning to sing.

43:37.280 --> 43:39.200
The flowers had a sweet smell.

43:41.600 --> 43:43.840
It has been a strange night, Jane.

43:44.640 --> 43:45.760
Mr. Rochester said.

43:46.720 --> 43:47.760
Were you frightened?

43:49.360 --> 43:52.320
I am frightened of Grace Poole, I said.

43:53.280 --> 43:54.800
She will hurt you one day.

43:56.480 --> 43:58.240
I am stronger than she is.

43:59.040 --> 44:00.160
She will not hurt me.

44:01.040 --> 44:02.240
Mr. Rochester said.

44:03.600 --> 44:05.280
He looked at me for a few moments.

44:07.120 --> 44:09.440
Are you my friend, Jane?

44:10.320 --> 44:11.040
He asked me.

44:12.160 --> 44:12.800
Yes, sir.

44:13.600 --> 44:15.200
I will be your friend forever.

44:16.160 --> 44:16.800
I replied.

44:18.400 --> 44:20.080
Thank you, my dear.

44:21.040 --> 44:22.240
Mr. Rochester said.

44:23.280 --> 44:24.560
I have made mistakes.

44:25.600 --> 44:27.280
Now I want to be happy.

44:28.480 --> 44:30.960
That is not wrong, is it, Jane?

44:32.560 --> 44:34.080
He stopped speaking for a minute.

44:34.720 --> 44:35.840
Then he said.

44:37.520 --> 44:38.560
Go into the house.

44:39.440 --> 44:40.640
I will talk to you tomorrow.

44:43.440 --> 44:44.400
But the next day,

44:45.040 --> 44:46.800
I had a letter from Gates Head Hall.

44:47.440 --> 44:48.800
My aunt reads House.

44:50.000 --> 44:52.400
The letter was from my cousin Eliza.

44:54.800 --> 44:55.760
Gates Head Hall.

44:57.120 --> 44:58.400
Dear Jane Eyre.

44:59.920 --> 45:02.800
My brother, John, is dead.

45:04.080 --> 45:05.440
My mother is very ill.

45:06.800 --> 45:08.160
She wants to speak to you.

45:09.360 --> 45:10.960
Please come quickly, Jane.

45:12.160 --> 45:14.320
Your cousin, Eliza Reed.

45:16.480 --> 45:19.760
I started the journey to my aunt reads House immediately.

45:21.200 --> 45:22.640
I arrived there the next day.

45:24.320 --> 45:26.640
My aunt Reed was very, very ill.

45:27.840 --> 45:28.800
She could not move.

45:29.920 --> 45:31.280
And she did not speak to me.

45:32.240 --> 45:34.960
I wanted to return to Thornfield Hall.

45:36.320 --> 45:38.080
I wanted to see Mr. Rochester.

45:39.440 --> 45:42.080
But Eliza wanted me to stay at Gates Head Hall.

45:45.440 --> 45:46.480
After three weeks,

45:47.280 --> 45:49.040
my aunt spoke to me at last.

45:50.080 --> 45:52.000
She spoke very slowly.

45:54.080 --> 45:56.720
Are you, Jane Eyre?

45:57.840 --> 45:58.480
She asked.

45:59.360 --> 46:01.280
Yes, Aunt Reed.

46:02.160 --> 46:03.440
I am Jane Eyre.

46:04.560 --> 46:05.280
I replied.

46:07.360 --> 46:09.840
There is a letter for you,

46:10.640 --> 46:11.680
Aunt Reed said.

46:13.040 --> 46:14.400
It is in my desk.

46:15.920 --> 46:17.200
Cora Eliza, please.

46:18.320 --> 46:20.080
She will get the letter.

46:21.840 --> 46:23.280
Eliza came into the room.

46:24.240 --> 46:27.280
She opened the desk and she gave me a letter.

46:29.360 --> 46:30.720
Read the letter, Jane.

46:31.920 --> 46:32.720
My aunt said.

46:34.320 --> 46:36.160
The letter had come from Madeira,

46:37.040 --> 46:38.880
but it was three years old.

46:40.880 --> 46:44.480
Madeira, October, 1831.

46:46.480 --> 46:47.280
Dear Madam,

46:48.400 --> 46:50.000
I am Jane Eyre's uncle.

46:50.960 --> 46:52.400
I am a very rich man.

46:53.600 --> 46:54.720
I have no children.

46:55.520 --> 46:58.720
One day, Jane will have all my money.

46:59.920 --> 47:00.960
Tell her about me.

47:01.760 --> 47:03.040
She must write to me.

47:04.320 --> 47:05.280
John Eyre.

47:07.680 --> 47:10.240
I answered that letter.

47:11.280 --> 47:12.240
Aunt Reed said.

47:13.520 --> 47:14.960
I hated you, Jane.

47:16.000 --> 47:18.560
I did not want you to have your uncle's money.

47:20.160 --> 47:21.360
I wrote to John Eyre.

47:22.320 --> 47:25.280
I wrote, Jane Eyre is dead.

47:26.320 --> 47:28.320
She died at lowwood school.

47:30.160 --> 47:31.760
I am sorry, Jane.

47:33.200 --> 47:34.160
I was wrong.

47:37.200 --> 47:39.040
Mrs. Reed died that night.

47:40.560 --> 47:42.880
I left Gates Head Hall a few days later.

47:44.000 --> 47:45.760
I took my uncle's letter with me.

47:48.000 --> 47:50.640
Mr. Rochester met me at Thornfield Hall.

47:52.320 --> 47:55.040
Welcome back to my house, he said.

47:56.160 --> 47:58.080
This is your home, Jane.

47:59.200 --> 48:00.000
Thank you, sir.

48:00.720 --> 48:03.200
I said, I am very happy here.

48:04.880 --> 48:06.960
Mr. Rochester's guests had left.

48:08.080 --> 48:10.480
No other visitors came to Thornfield Hall.

48:11.920 --> 48:15.600
Every day, Mr. Rochester and I talked together.

48:17.120 --> 48:20.240
And every day, I loved him more.

48:21.360 --> 48:28.600
The

48:34.120 --> 48:34.880
Chapter 8

48:36.320 --> 48:37.200
In the Garden

48:39.440 --> 48:41.680
In June, the weather was hot.

48:43.040 --> 48:45.680
One evening, I walked into the garden.

48:47.120 --> 48:48.800
Mr. Rochester was there too.

48:49.440 --> 48:52.720
Do you like this house, Jane?

48:53.520 --> 48:57.360
He asked, yes, sir, I replied.

48:59.040 --> 49:02.400
Soon, Adele will go to live at a school, Jane.

49:03.280 --> 49:07.440
He said, then I will not want to govern us here.

49:08.800 --> 49:10.160
Will you be sad, then, Jane?

49:11.120 --> 49:12.800
Will you leave Thornfield Hall?

49:14.160 --> 49:16.080
Leave, I said quickly.

49:17.040 --> 49:18.720
Must I leave Thornfield?

49:20.080 --> 49:23.360
My dear, Mr. Rochester stopped.

49:24.320 --> 49:25.760
He was silent for a moment.

49:27.040 --> 49:31.040
Then he said, I am going to be married soon.

49:32.560 --> 49:37.760
Oh, sir, I said, then I must go far away.

49:38.800 --> 49:42.560
Far away from Thornfield, far away from you, sir.

49:43.840 --> 49:44.960
I started to cry.

49:46.960 --> 49:49.040
I will always remember you, Jane.

49:49.680 --> 49:53.040
Mr. Rochester said, will you forget me?

49:54.160 --> 49:56.240
No, sir, I replied.

49:56.800 --> 49:58.240
I will never forget you.

49:58.960 --> 50:01.200
I don't want to leave Thornfield, sir.

50:01.760 --> 50:02.960
I don't want to leave you.

50:04.800 --> 50:06.000
Don't leave, Jane.

50:06.800 --> 50:09.760
Mr. Rochester said, stay here.

50:11.120 --> 50:12.160
He smiled at me.

50:13.440 --> 50:15.040
I must not stay here, sir.

50:15.600 --> 50:18.480
I said, you are going to marry Miss Ingram.

50:19.680 --> 50:20.480
I am poor.

50:21.200 --> 50:22.640
I do not have a pretty face.

50:24.000 --> 50:25.120
But I have a heart.

50:26.240 --> 50:27.920
It is a loving heart, sir.

50:29.840 --> 50:33.280
Jane, I am not going to marry Miss Ingram.

50:34.080 --> 50:35.360
Mr. Rochester said,

50:36.880 --> 50:37.760
she is rich.

50:38.560 --> 50:39.520
She is beautiful.

50:40.640 --> 50:41.440
You are poor.

50:42.240 --> 50:43.520
You are not beautiful.

50:44.160 --> 50:46.320
But I want to marry you.

50:47.600 --> 50:49.840
Will you marry me, Jane?

50:51.200 --> 50:54.000
For a moment, I could not speak.

50:55.200 --> 50:57.120
At last, I asked,

50:58.480 --> 51:00.240
do you love me, sir?

51:01.440 --> 51:04.000
I do, he replied.

51:05.280 --> 51:09.760
Then, sir, I will marry you, I said.

51:10.960 --> 51:13.040
And Mr. Rochester kissed me.

51:14.320 --> 51:17.760
My dearest Jane, he said,

51:18.800 --> 51:20.640
nothing can stop our marriage now.

51:21.600 --> 51:23.440
We will be married in a month, Jane.

51:24.800 --> 51:25.680
We kissed again.

51:27.200 --> 51:28.640
Then, I said goodnight,

51:29.280 --> 51:30.560
and I went into the house.

51:31.920 --> 51:33.520
I went upstairs to my room.

51:35.040 --> 51:38.640
Later, I remembered my Uncle John Eyre's letter.

51:40.080 --> 51:41.760
I will write to him in Madeira.

51:42.720 --> 51:43.760
I said to myself,

51:44.640 --> 51:47.920
I will tell him about my marriage to Mr. Rochester.

51:49.040 --> 51:50.240
I am very happy.

51:51.280 --> 51:52.960
My Uncle will be happy too.

51:55.360 --> 51:56.640
Four weeks passed.

51:57.920 --> 52:01.120
Mr. Rochester was going to buy me many beautiful things.

52:02.000 --> 52:03.920
He was going to give me many presents.

52:05.440 --> 52:07.200
But I did not want these things.

52:07.920 --> 52:10.000
No, Edward, I said.

52:11.520 --> 52:13.120
I am not beautiful.

52:14.000 --> 52:16.000
I don't want beautiful things.

52:17.120 --> 52:19.360
I want you, Edward.

52:22.160 --> 52:23.920
It was the month of July,

52:24.880 --> 52:26.800
two days before our wedding day,

52:27.280 --> 52:29.200
Mr. Rochester went away.

52:30.880 --> 52:33.440
I will return tomorrow, he said.

52:34.240 --> 52:35.840
I love you, Jane.

52:38.160 --> 52:40.800
That night, I went to my bedroom early.

52:41.920 --> 52:45.120
My wedding dress and my wedding veil were in my room.

52:46.080 --> 52:46.880
I looked at them.

52:48.720 --> 52:52.480
In two days, I will beat Jane, Rochester.

52:53.280 --> 52:56.640
I said to myself, then I went to bed.

52:58.080 --> 52:59.680
But I did not sleep well.

53:01.840 --> 53:04.640
The next day, Mr. Rochester returned.

53:05.520 --> 53:06.960
He looked at me carefully.

53:08.960 --> 53:10.320
What is wrong, Jane?

53:10.880 --> 53:13.600
He asked, your face is pale.

53:14.640 --> 53:15.600
Are you frightened?

53:17.600 --> 53:19.920
I had a very strange dream last night.

53:20.880 --> 53:24.720
I said, it was a dream about this house.

53:26.000 --> 53:29.600
But in my dream, Thornfield Hall had no roof.

53:30.400 --> 53:31.600
The walls were burnt.

53:32.400 --> 53:33.040
They were black.

53:33.920 --> 53:36.880
In my dream, I tried to find you,

53:37.760 --> 53:39.200
but you were not in the house.

53:40.800 --> 53:42.880
Are you afraid of a dream, Jane?

53:43.760 --> 53:45.200
Mr. Rochester asked.

53:46.640 --> 53:49.280
No, Edward, I replied.

53:50.160 --> 53:51.760
But I woke up from my dream.

53:52.480 --> 53:54.000
There was a woman in my room.

53:54.880 --> 53:56.720
She was tall and heavy.

53:57.440 --> 53:59.040
She had long black hair.

53:59.920 --> 54:03.760
The woman was holding a candle, I said.

54:03.760 --> 54:06.240
She put the candle by my mirror.

54:07.680 --> 54:10.160
She put my wedging veil over her head,

54:10.160 --> 54:11.760
and she looked in the mirror.

54:12.960 --> 54:15.360
Then I saw her face.

54:16.400 --> 54:19.680
It was a strange, terrible face, Edward.

54:20.480 --> 54:26.080
I said, suddenly, the woman tore my veil into two pieces.

54:26.400 --> 54:29.760
She threw the pieces on the floor.

54:31.920 --> 54:33.360
What happened next?

54:34.400 --> 54:35.680
Mr. Rochester asked.

54:36.880 --> 54:39.520
The woman held her candle near my face.

54:40.480 --> 54:41.120
I replied.

54:42.080 --> 54:44.400
She looked at me, and she laughed.

54:45.840 --> 54:46.880
Then she went away.

54:48.960 --> 54:51.200
This happened in your dream, Jane.

54:52.000 --> 54:53.120
Mr. Rochester said,

54:54.080 --> 54:56.240
he did not happen in my dream, Edward.

54:57.280 --> 55:02.160
I said, this morning, my wedding veil was on the floor of my room.

55:02.800 --> 55:03.600
It was torn.

55:04.400 --> 55:05.680
It was in two pieces.

55:07.360 --> 55:10.160
But the woman did not hurt you, Jane.

55:11.040 --> 55:12.240
Mr. Rochester said,

55:13.520 --> 55:16.240
sleep in a doll's room tonight, my dear.

55:17.360 --> 55:19.200
You will have no more bad dreams.

55:24.080 --> 55:26.080
You will have no more bad dreams.

55:29.520 --> 55:30.400
Chapter 9

55:31.920 --> 55:33.520
Mr. Rochester's wife.

55:36.400 --> 55:37.840
It was our wedding day.

55:39.040 --> 55:42.160
We were going to be married in a church near Thornfield Hall.

55:43.440 --> 55:46.560
After the marriage, we were going to travel to London.

55:48.320 --> 55:49.200
I got up early.

55:50.000 --> 55:52.880
I put on my wedding dress, and I went downstairs.

55:54.000 --> 55:55.840
Mr. Rochester was waiting for me.

55:57.120 --> 56:00.160
At eight o'clock, we walked together to the church.

56:01.360 --> 56:03.920
The clergyman was standing by the door of the church.

56:05.360 --> 56:08.880
There were two other people inside the church, two men.

56:09.840 --> 56:11.520
They were sitting in a dark corner.

56:12.480 --> 56:14.000
I could not see them very well.

56:15.680 --> 56:17.520
The clergyman started to speak.

56:18.640 --> 56:22.640
At every marriage, the clergyman asks an important question.

56:23.680 --> 56:25.680
He asks the people in the church.

56:26.720 --> 56:28.800
Is there a problem about this marriage?

56:30.640 --> 56:32.560
The clergyman spoke loudly.

56:33.440 --> 56:36.240
He asked this question, and he waited.

56:37.760 --> 56:39.440
There was silence for a moment.

56:40.560 --> 56:44.240
And then, one of the men in the dark corner stood up.

56:45.360 --> 56:46.560
He spoke loudly.

56:47.360 --> 56:49.440
There is a problem.

56:50.080 --> 56:52.800
These two people must not be married.

56:53.520 --> 56:54.000
He said.

56:55.360 --> 56:56.800
There is not a problem.

56:57.520 --> 56:59.440
Mr. Rochester said to the clergyman,

57:00.240 --> 57:01.920
please go on with the marriage.

57:03.200 --> 57:06.720
No, I cannot go on with the marriage.

57:07.360 --> 57:08.560
The clergyman replied.

57:09.440 --> 57:11.200
He spoke to the man in the corner.

57:12.400 --> 57:14.560
What is the problem, sir?

57:15.360 --> 57:16.080
He asked.

57:17.680 --> 57:21.200
Mr. Edward Rochester has a wife.

57:23.440 --> 57:26.480
Mr. Rochester turned and looked at the man.

57:27.920 --> 57:28.720
Who are you?

57:29.600 --> 57:30.880
What do you know about me?

57:31.920 --> 57:33.280
He asked angrily.

57:34.640 --> 57:36.560
My name is Briggs, sir.

57:37.120 --> 57:38.000
I am a lawyer.

57:38.800 --> 57:39.680
The man replied.

57:40.640 --> 57:42.480
I know many things about you.

57:43.440 --> 57:46.560
15 years ago, you were married in the West Indies.

57:47.520 --> 57:50.720
Your wife's name is Bertha Mason.

57:51.760 --> 57:52.720
She is alive.

57:53.520 --> 57:56.080
She lives at Thornfield Hall.

57:57.760 --> 57:59.200
How do you know that?

58:00.000 --> 58:01.440
Mr. Rochester shouted.

58:02.400 --> 58:04.720
The other man in the dark corner stood up.

58:05.520 --> 58:06.640
He walked towards us.

58:07.680 --> 58:09.120
It was Richard Mason.

58:10.080 --> 58:13.360
Bertha Mason is my sister, he said.

58:14.000 --> 58:18.000
I saw her at Thornfield Hall in April.

58:19.440 --> 58:21.440
Mr. Rochester's face was pale.

58:22.400 --> 58:24.640
For a minute, he was silent.

58:26.160 --> 58:27.760
Then he spoke quietly.

58:29.920 --> 58:32.400
It is true, he said.

58:33.680 --> 58:36.000
My wife is living at Thornfield Hall.

58:37.200 --> 58:37.920
She is mad.

58:39.200 --> 58:40.800
Come to the house, all of you.

58:41.680 --> 58:43.920
Come and see Mrs. Rochester.

58:44.560 --> 58:46.320
Come and see the mad woman.

58:49.040 --> 58:50.240
We all left the church.

58:51.440 --> 58:52.320
Nobody spoke.

58:54.560 --> 58:58.720
At Thornfield, Mrs. Fairfax and Adele were waiting for us.

58:59.680 --> 59:01.120
They were smiling happily.

59:02.640 --> 59:04.240
Nobody will be happy today.

59:05.120 --> 59:06.320
Mr. Rochester said,

59:07.120 --> 59:08.800
We are not married.

59:10.480 --> 59:15.360
Briggs, Mr. Mason, the clergyman and I followed Mr. Rochester.

59:16.880 --> 59:18.400
We followed him up the stairs.

59:19.760 --> 59:21.520
He took us to the top corridor.

59:22.800 --> 59:26.320
He unlocked the door and we went into a small room.

59:27.840 --> 59:29.520
I had seen this room before.

59:31.200 --> 59:33.280
We walked through the room to another door.

59:34.240 --> 59:38.000
Mr. Rochester unlocked this door and we saw a larger room.

59:39.680 --> 59:41.600
Grace Poole was sitting in the room.

59:42.640 --> 59:44.320
But another woman was there too.

59:45.520 --> 59:47.200
She was tall and heavy.

59:48.080 --> 59:50.400
Her dark hair was in front of her face.

59:51.760 --> 59:53.520
The woman turned and looked at us.

59:55.200 --> 59:57.920
I knew that terrible, mad face.

59:59.200 --> 01:00:02.560
I had seen it in my bedroom two nights before.

01:00:04.160 --> 01:00:07.200
The mad woman saw Mr. Rochester.

01:00:08.320 --> 01:00:10.800
She screamed and she ran towards him.

01:00:12.000 --> 01:00:13.120
Be careful, sir.

01:00:13.920 --> 01:00:14.880
Grace Poole said.

01:00:15.920 --> 01:00:17.600
The mad woman was very strong.

01:00:18.400 --> 01:00:21.040
She screamed and she hit Mr. Rochester.

01:00:22.080 --> 01:00:24.480
But Mr. Rochester held her arms.

01:00:26.880 --> 01:00:29.680
This woman is my wife.

01:00:30.720 --> 01:00:32.320
Mr. Rochester said angrily.

01:00:33.360 --> 01:00:35.360
I wanted to forget about her.

01:00:36.080 --> 01:00:39.520
I wanted to marry this young girl, Jane Eyre.

01:00:40.400 --> 01:00:41.280
Was I wrong?

01:00:43.280 --> 01:00:45.200
He was silent for a few moments.

01:00:46.560 --> 01:00:48.400
Then he spoke quietly.

01:00:50.400 --> 01:00:53.200
Yes, I was wrong.

01:00:54.320 --> 01:00:59.680
He said, I love Jane Eyre, but I was wrong.

01:00:59.920 --> 01:01:01.440
Now go.

01:01:01.440 --> 01:01:03.440
All of you.

01:01:04.640 --> 01:01:07.040
I must take care of my mad wife.

01:01:10.880 --> 01:01:12.560
I went slowly downstairs.

01:01:14.080 --> 01:01:16.800
Mr. Briggs, the lawyer, spoke to me.

01:01:18.880 --> 01:01:21.440
I am sorry for you, Miss Eyre.

01:01:22.240 --> 01:01:25.600
He said, you did nothing wrong.

01:01:26.560 --> 01:01:29.200
Your uncle, John Eyre, is sorry for you too.

01:01:30.320 --> 01:01:35.280
He read your letter and then he met Richard Mason in Madeira.

01:01:36.880 --> 01:01:39.360
Your uncle is dying, Miss Eyre.

01:01:40.640 --> 01:01:42.400
He could not come to England.

01:01:44.000 --> 01:01:45.200
He sent me here.

01:01:46.320 --> 01:01:48.160
He wanted me to stop this marriage.

01:01:51.200 --> 01:01:52.240
I did not answer.

01:01:53.280 --> 01:01:56.080
I went to my room and I locked the door.

01:01:56.320 --> 01:01:59.520
I took off my wedding dress.

01:02:01.040 --> 01:02:03.120
I put on a plain black dress.

01:02:05.440 --> 01:02:06.720
I lay down on my bed.

01:02:09.760 --> 01:02:13.200
I am Jane Eyre today, I thought.

01:02:14.640 --> 01:02:16.400
I will be Jane Eyre tomorrow.

01:02:18.480 --> 01:02:20.240
I will never be Jane Rochester.

01:02:21.600 --> 01:02:23.600
I must leave Thornfield Hall.

01:02:24.400 --> 01:02:27.200
I must never see Mr. Rochester again.

01:02:28.320 --> 01:02:29.920
My life here is finished.

01:02:32.720 --> 01:02:35.600
Many hours later, I got off the bed.

01:02:36.720 --> 01:02:37.920
I unlocked my door.

01:02:39.680 --> 01:02:42.240
Mr. Rochester was waiting outside my room.

01:02:44.640 --> 01:02:46.080
You are unhappy, Jane.

01:02:46.960 --> 01:02:50.560
He said, I am very, very sorry.

01:02:51.360 --> 01:02:54.880
Jane, we will leave Thornfield.

01:02:55.680 --> 01:02:57.120
We will go to another country.

01:02:58.000 --> 01:02:59.280
We will be happy again.

01:03:00.880 --> 01:03:02.160
I cannot be your wife.

01:03:03.280 --> 01:03:04.560
I cannot live with you.

01:03:05.440 --> 01:03:08.880
I said, I must leave you, Edward.

01:03:10.640 --> 01:03:14.000
Listen, Jane, Mr. Rochester said.

01:03:15.600 --> 01:03:18.240
My father wanted me to marry both the Mason.

01:03:19.200 --> 01:03:20.800
Her family was very rich.

01:03:22.000 --> 01:03:22.880
I married her.

01:03:23.840 --> 01:03:25.200
My father was happy.

01:03:26.720 --> 01:03:28.320
But I was not happy.

01:03:29.440 --> 01:03:33.200
Bertha was mad and she was a bad woman.

01:03:34.400 --> 01:03:36.000
Nobody told me about her.

01:03:36.960 --> 01:03:40.400
She was married to me, but she met other men.

01:03:41.360 --> 01:03:42.800
She was drunk every day.

01:03:43.840 --> 01:03:46.080
She tried to kill me many times.

01:03:48.320 --> 01:03:52.560
After four years, I brought Bertha here to Thornfield Hall.

01:03:53.600 --> 01:03:57.840
Mr. Rochester said, then I went away.

01:03:59.520 --> 01:04:01.360
Grace Poole took care of Bertha.

01:04:02.720 --> 01:04:03.840
I met other women.

01:04:05.200 --> 01:04:06.880
One of them was a French singer.

01:04:07.920 --> 01:04:09.200
She was a Dell's mother.

01:04:10.480 --> 01:04:12.400
A Dell is my daughter, Jane.

01:04:13.600 --> 01:04:15.600
But I did not love the French singer.

01:04:16.320 --> 01:04:17.840
I did not love anybody.

01:04:19.200 --> 01:04:21.120
I came home to Thornfield Hall.

01:04:23.040 --> 01:04:25.920
Then you came here and I loved you.

01:04:27.840 --> 01:04:29.040
I will always love you.

01:04:30.720 --> 01:04:32.400
Please stay with me, Jane.

01:04:34.320 --> 01:04:35.120
No, Edward.

01:04:35.920 --> 01:04:38.160
I said, I am going away.

01:04:39.520 --> 01:04:43.600
We will be unhappy, but we must not be together.

01:04:44.400 --> 01:04:46.800
Goodbye, Edward.

01:04:48.400 --> 01:04:51.200
Oh, Jane, Jane, my love.

01:04:52.160 --> 01:04:55.200
Mr. Rochester said, don't leave me.

01:04:56.720 --> 01:04:58.320
I kissed Mr. Rochester.

01:04:59.920 --> 01:05:01.440
God will help you, Edward.

01:05:02.480 --> 01:05:07.520
I said, quickly, I went into my room.

01:05:08.400 --> 01:05:10.160
I put some clothes into a bag.

01:05:10.800 --> 01:05:14.560
Later, I heard Mr. Rochester go into his room.

01:05:15.840 --> 01:05:18.480
Very quietly, I went downstairs.

01:05:19.600 --> 01:05:22.080
I opened the small door at the side of the house.

01:05:23.520 --> 01:05:27.280
I left Thornfield Hall and I walked to the road.

01:05:28.400 --> 01:05:29.200
It was dark.

01:05:30.800 --> 01:05:33.040
Soon, a coach came along the road.

01:05:34.160 --> 01:05:36.480
I gave all my money to the driver of the coach.

01:05:37.680 --> 01:05:38.880
I got into the coach.

01:05:40.880 --> 01:05:46.160
Many hours later, the coach stopped.

01:05:47.120 --> 01:05:48.800
It was 10 o'clock in the morning.

01:05:50.320 --> 01:05:52.320
You must give me more money now.

01:05:53.120 --> 01:05:56.560
The driver said, I have no more money.

01:05:57.200 --> 01:06:00.080
I said, you have no more money.

01:06:00.800 --> 01:06:02.720
Then you must get out of the coach.

01:06:03.600 --> 01:06:07.600
The driver said, I got down onto the road.

01:06:08.560 --> 01:06:10.240
The coach moved away quickly.

01:06:11.280 --> 01:06:13.440
But I had left my back in the coach.

01:06:15.040 --> 01:06:16.080
I looked around me.

01:06:17.040 --> 01:06:19.360
I was on a cold, empty moor.

01:06:20.480 --> 01:06:22.320
I was tired and hungry.

01:06:23.680 --> 01:06:25.200
I walked and walked.

01:06:26.320 --> 01:06:27.440
I had no money.

01:06:28.320 --> 01:06:29.520
I had no food.

01:06:30.880 --> 01:06:32.720
I walked until the evening came.

01:06:34.160 --> 01:06:37.200
At last, I lay down on the ground.

01:06:38.560 --> 01:06:40.400
I fell asleep immediately.

01:06:50.560 --> 01:06:51.440
Chapter 10.

01:06:53.200 --> 01:06:54.080
More House

01:06:57.280 --> 01:06:59.840
The next morning, I woke late.

01:07:00.960 --> 01:07:03.120
I walked along the road for many miles.

01:07:04.160 --> 01:07:05.440
It started to rain.

01:07:06.240 --> 01:07:08.480
Soon, my clothes were wet.

01:07:09.600 --> 01:07:10.800
I saw no one.

01:07:11.760 --> 01:07:13.520
I walked on the moor all day.

01:07:15.200 --> 01:07:18.400
In the evening, I was very tired again.

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:22.800
I must sleep soon, I thought.

01:07:23.760 --> 01:07:24.960
Where shall I sleep?

01:07:26.560 --> 01:07:28.320
Then, I saw a light.

01:07:29.360 --> 01:07:31.120
I walked slowly towards it.

01:07:32.160 --> 01:07:34.000
The rain was falling heavily.

01:07:35.520 --> 01:07:37.440
But I saw a house near the road.

01:07:38.800 --> 01:07:40.160
I walked up to the house.

01:07:41.040 --> 01:07:42.080
I knocked on the door.

01:07:43.360 --> 01:07:46.000
I waited, but nobody opened the door.

01:07:47.360 --> 01:07:48.800
I stood outside the house.

01:07:49.920 --> 01:07:52.960
I was very cold and very tired.

01:07:54.160 --> 01:07:55.120
I could not move.

01:07:57.200 --> 01:07:59.120
I am going to die here.

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:04.720
I said, then I heard a young man's voice.

01:08:05.840 --> 01:08:07.680
The man was standing behind me.

01:08:09.440 --> 01:08:13.680
No, you will not die at more house, the man said.

01:08:14.640 --> 01:08:17.040
Then, he unlocked the door of the house.

01:08:18.160 --> 01:08:19.440
He took me into the house.

01:08:20.480 --> 01:08:23.040
He took me into a warm, sitting room.

01:08:24.640 --> 01:08:26.960
Please sit down, he said.

01:08:28.240 --> 01:08:30.480
Two pretty young women came into the room.

01:08:32.080 --> 01:08:34.720
Give this poor woman some fool, Diana.

01:08:35.440 --> 01:08:39.280
The young man said, give us some dry clothes, Mary.

01:08:40.560 --> 01:08:42.000
Then he spoke to me again.

01:08:43.600 --> 01:08:46.400
My name is Singing Rivers, he said.

01:08:47.120 --> 01:08:50.160
These are my sisters, Diana and Mary.

01:08:51.200 --> 01:08:53.120
What is your name, young woman?

01:08:54.800 --> 01:08:55.840
My name is Jane.

01:08:57.200 --> 01:08:58.800
Elliot, I said.

01:09:00.160 --> 01:09:01.360
I closed my eyes.

01:09:02.240 --> 01:09:05.440
Jane is very tired, Diana said.

01:09:05.920 --> 01:09:07.600
She must go to bed now.

01:09:09.040 --> 01:09:12.240
I stayed in bed at more house for three days.

01:09:15.040 --> 01:09:17.440
Diana and Mary Rivers were governesses.

01:09:18.480 --> 01:09:20.960
They were staying at more house for a few days.

01:09:22.000 --> 01:09:24.800
Singing, their brother, was a clergyman.

01:09:25.600 --> 01:09:27.200
They were very kind to me.

01:09:27.840 --> 01:09:30.240
Soon, we were good friends.

01:09:32.160 --> 01:09:35.840
One day, Singing asked me about my life.

01:09:37.680 --> 01:09:40.400
I was a governess too, I told him.

01:09:41.440 --> 01:09:43.520
And I told him about Lowwood School.

01:09:44.720 --> 01:09:47.280
But I did not tell him about Thornfield Hall.

01:09:48.480 --> 01:09:50.800
I did not tell him about Mr. Rochester.

01:09:52.960 --> 01:09:54.480
I want to work, Singing.

01:09:55.120 --> 01:09:57.200
I said, will you help me?

01:09:58.080 --> 01:10:00.800
I have a plan, Singing said.

01:10:01.520 --> 01:10:04.320
A few miles from here, there is a village.

01:10:04.880 --> 01:10:07.760
Many of the girls in the village cannot read or write.

01:10:08.400 --> 01:10:11.360
I am going to pay for a girl's school in the village.

01:10:12.160 --> 01:10:14.800
But I must find a teacher for these girls.

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:17.840
I will teach them, Singing.

01:10:18.400 --> 01:10:21.360
I said, good, he said.

01:10:21.840 --> 01:10:24.240
There will be a small house next to the school.

01:10:24.800 --> 01:10:26.240
You will live there.

01:10:28.160 --> 01:10:31.280
Three days later, a letter arrived for Singing.

01:10:33.120 --> 01:10:37.600
Diana, Mary, our uncle John is dead.

01:10:38.320 --> 01:10:42.720
He told his sisters, but we will not have any of his money.

01:10:44.480 --> 01:10:46.240
He gave the letter to his sisters.

01:10:47.040 --> 01:10:47.680
They read it.

01:10:49.120 --> 01:10:52.640
Uncle John was our muppest brother, Diana told me.

01:10:53.520 --> 01:10:58.000
He was very rich, but he has given all his money to another niece.

01:10:58.960 --> 01:11:00.000
We do not know her.

01:11:02.160 --> 01:11:04.240
Soon, I went to live in the village.

01:11:05.040 --> 01:11:07.040
I lived in the house next to the school.

01:11:08.240 --> 01:11:10.320
Every day, I taught the girls.

01:11:11.120 --> 01:11:12.560
My pupils worked hard.

01:11:13.840 --> 01:11:15.040
But I was not happy.

01:11:16.320 --> 01:11:18.960
Every day, I thought about Edward Rochester.

01:11:18.960 --> 01:11:22.560
Does he think about me?

01:11:23.520 --> 01:11:24.560
I asked myself.

01:11:26.400 --> 01:11:27.680
Four months passed.

01:11:28.960 --> 01:11:31.840
One day, Singing rivers came to my house.

01:11:32.640 --> 01:11:33.760
He was holding a letter.

01:11:34.640 --> 01:11:35.440
He was worried.

01:11:37.200 --> 01:11:37.920
What is wrong?

01:11:38.480 --> 01:11:39.120
I asked.

01:11:40.720 --> 01:11:42.880
I want to ask you three questions, Jane.

01:11:43.600 --> 01:11:44.320
He replied.

01:11:45.440 --> 01:11:47.200
Is your name Jane Elliot?

01:11:48.160 --> 01:11:49.600
Do you have another name?

01:11:50.720 --> 01:11:52.640
Do you know Jane Eyre?

01:11:54.560 --> 01:11:56.000
I looked at him for a moment.

01:11:56.800 --> 01:11:57.840
I did not speak.

01:11:59.840 --> 01:12:01.760
I have some news for Jane Eyre,

01:12:02.320 --> 01:12:03.120
Singing said.

01:12:04.080 --> 01:12:06.320
Jane Eyre was a pupil at Lowood School,

01:12:07.200 --> 01:12:08.560
and she was a teacher there.

01:12:09.760 --> 01:12:12.640
Then she was a governess at Thornfield Hall,

01:12:13.520 --> 01:12:15.760
the home of Mr. Edward Rochester.

01:12:17.600 --> 01:12:18.640
How do you know this?

01:12:19.200 --> 01:12:19.840
I asked.

01:12:20.720 --> 01:12:22.640
What do you know about Mr. Rochester?

01:12:23.600 --> 01:12:24.240
How is he?

01:12:25.920 --> 01:12:28.240
I don't know, Singing said.

01:12:29.040 --> 01:12:30.800
This letter is from a lawyer.

01:12:31.680 --> 01:12:34.480
The lawyer tells a story about Mr. Rochester.

01:12:35.360 --> 01:12:37.280
Mr. Rochester had a mad wife,

01:12:38.240 --> 01:12:40.000
but he tried to marry Jane Eyre.

01:12:40.880 --> 01:12:42.400
She left Thornfield.

01:12:43.440 --> 01:12:45.840
Now this lawyer, Mr. Briggs,

01:12:46.400 --> 01:12:47.600
is trying to find her.

01:12:49.520 --> 01:12:51.280
I will tell you the truth, Singing.

01:12:51.920 --> 01:12:52.400
I said.

01:12:53.600 --> 01:12:55.520
My name is not Jane Elliot.

01:12:56.480 --> 01:12:57.920
My name is Jane Eyre,

01:12:59.040 --> 01:13:01.440
and I was a governess at Thornfield Hall.

01:13:02.880 --> 01:13:04.400
I know Mr. Rochester.

01:13:06.000 --> 01:13:08.880
Did Mr. Briggs write anything about Mr. Rochester?

01:13:10.240 --> 01:13:10.480
No.

01:13:11.440 --> 01:13:14.320
The letter is about you, Jane, Singing said.

01:13:15.200 --> 01:13:17.440
Your uncle, John Eyre, is dead.

01:13:18.400 --> 01:13:21.360
John Eyre has given you 20,000 pounds.

01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:23.120
You are rich, Jane.

01:13:24.640 --> 01:13:26.880
But why did Mr. Briggs write to you?

01:13:27.440 --> 01:13:28.160
I asked.

01:13:29.360 --> 01:13:32.560
My mother's name was Eyre, Singing said.

01:13:33.200 --> 01:13:35.120
She was your father's sister, Jane.

01:13:36.480 --> 01:13:41.200
Then you, Diana and Mary, are my cousins, I said.

01:13:42.080 --> 01:13:44.400
I thought carefully for a moment.

01:13:45.840 --> 01:13:48.080
Write to Diana and Mary, I said.

01:13:49.200 --> 01:13:50.240
They must come home.

01:13:51.280 --> 01:13:54.240
I will give all of you some of Uncle John's money.

01:13:56.800 --> 01:13:59.440
The next day, I wrote to Mr. Briggs.

01:14:00.400 --> 01:14:05.280
I gave Singing, Diana and Mary, 5,000 pounds each.

01:14:06.560 --> 01:14:08.400
I wrote to Mrs. Fairfax, too.

01:14:09.360 --> 01:14:10.880
But she did not reply.

01:14:14.000 --> 01:14:15.360
Six months passed.

01:14:16.400 --> 01:14:18.640
I heard nothing from Thornfield Hall.

01:14:19.920 --> 01:14:22.080
I heard nothing about Mr. Rochester.

01:14:24.080 --> 01:14:28.000
Then, one day, I was walking on the moor.

01:14:29.440 --> 01:14:31.520
Suddenly, I heard a voice.

01:14:32.720 --> 01:14:34.160
There was nobody on the moor.

01:14:35.200 --> 01:14:37.040
But the voice was calling my name.

01:14:37.840 --> 01:14:41.040
Jane, Jane, Jane.

01:14:43.040 --> 01:14:45.040
That is Mr. Rochester's voice.

01:14:45.840 --> 01:14:49.120
I said to myself, then I shouted.

01:14:49.920 --> 01:14:51.440
I am coming, Edward.

01:14:52.000 --> 01:14:53.120
I am coming.

01:14:55.360 --> 01:14:56.720
I ran to Moorhouse.

01:14:57.440 --> 01:14:58.880
I spoke to my cousins.

01:14:59.920 --> 01:15:02.160
I am going to Thornfield Hall tomorrow.

01:15:02.800 --> 01:15:03.440
I told them.

01:15:04.400 --> 01:15:06.240
I began my journey the next day.

01:15:07.680 --> 01:15:29.920
I was standing on the road near Thornfield Hall.

01:15:31.120 --> 01:15:32.560
I ran across the fields.

01:15:33.760 --> 01:15:35.920
Was Mr. Rochester at Thornfield?

01:15:36.720 --> 01:15:37.440
Was he ill?

01:15:39.680 --> 01:15:41.280
And then I saw the house.

01:15:42.560 --> 01:15:43.920
The house had no roof.

01:15:45.040 --> 01:15:46.960
Its walls were burnt and black.

01:15:48.320 --> 01:15:49.680
Nobody was living there.

01:15:52.240 --> 01:15:54.480
I looked at the burnt black house.

01:15:55.680 --> 01:15:57.040
I had seen this before.

01:15:58.320 --> 01:15:59.840
I had seen it in a dream.

01:16:01.200 --> 01:16:02.160
I was frightened.

01:16:03.120 --> 01:16:04.720
Where was Edward Rochester?

01:16:06.480 --> 01:16:07.920
I went to the village of Hay.

01:16:09.040 --> 01:16:10.800
I asked about Thornfield Hall.

01:16:11.840 --> 01:16:13.680
I asked about Mr. Rochester.

01:16:15.840 --> 01:16:19.920
Three months ago, there was a fire at Thornfield Hall.

01:16:20.800 --> 01:16:24.400
A man told me, the madwoman burnt the house.

01:16:25.120 --> 01:16:27.200
She was Mr. Rochester's wife.

01:16:28.480 --> 01:16:30.400
Was Mr. Rochester in the house?

01:16:31.040 --> 01:16:32.960
I asked, yes.

01:16:33.680 --> 01:16:34.480
He was there.

01:16:35.280 --> 01:16:36.160
The man replied.

01:16:36.960 --> 01:16:38.960
He tried to save his wife's life.

01:16:39.840 --> 01:16:41.440
He went into the burning house.

01:16:42.560 --> 01:16:44.720
But the madwoman jumped from the roof.

01:16:45.760 --> 01:16:46.480
She died.

01:16:48.080 --> 01:16:49.680
Was Mr. Rochester hurt?

01:16:50.640 --> 01:16:51.840
I asked quickly.

01:16:53.040 --> 01:16:55.680
Yes, he was badly hurt.

01:16:56.400 --> 01:16:59.200
The man said, he is blind.

01:16:59.760 --> 01:17:00.720
He can't see.

01:17:01.680 --> 01:17:04.800
And he has only one hand.

01:17:06.480 --> 01:17:07.120
Where is he?

01:17:07.840 --> 01:17:08.480
I asked.

01:17:09.200 --> 01:17:09.920
Where is he?

01:17:11.600 --> 01:17:13.440
He is living up Thorn Dean.

01:17:14.080 --> 01:17:17.520
It is an old house, about 30 miles away.

01:17:18.320 --> 01:17:19.120
The man said,

01:17:20.160 --> 01:17:21.600
Do you have a carriage?

01:17:21.600 --> 01:17:22.560
I asked.

01:17:22.560 --> 01:17:24.800
I must go to Thorn Dean immediately.

01:17:27.600 --> 01:17:29.760
I got out of the carriage near Thorn Dean.

01:17:30.720 --> 01:17:31.840
I walked to the house.

01:17:32.800 --> 01:17:33.920
I knocked on the door.

01:17:35.040 --> 01:17:36.400
A servant opened it.

01:17:37.440 --> 01:17:38.240
I knew her.

01:17:39.600 --> 01:17:41.360
Oh, Miss Eyre!

01:17:41.360 --> 01:17:42.240
You have come!

01:17:42.800 --> 01:17:43.280
She said,

01:17:44.080 --> 01:17:46.640
Mr. Rochester has been calling your name.

01:17:47.920 --> 01:17:49.680
A bell rang in another room.

01:17:50.720 --> 01:17:52.400
That is Mr. Rochester's bell.

01:17:52.960 --> 01:17:55.680
The woman said, he wants some candles.

01:17:55.920 --> 01:17:59.920
There were two candles on a table near the door.

01:18:00.880 --> 01:18:03.280
The woman lit them and she picked them up.

01:18:04.880 --> 01:18:06.640
Mr. Rochester is blind,

01:18:07.280 --> 01:18:10.320
but he always burns candles in his room in the evenings.

01:18:11.120 --> 01:18:11.600
She said,

01:18:13.040 --> 01:18:14.320
Give the candles to me.

01:18:15.120 --> 01:18:15.600
I said,

01:18:16.400 --> 01:18:17.520
I'll take them to him.

01:18:19.440 --> 01:18:21.760
I opened the door of Mr. Rochester's room.

01:18:22.720 --> 01:18:25.360
His black and white dog was sitting by the fire.

01:18:26.480 --> 01:18:29.600
The dog jumped up and ran towards me.

01:18:31.520 --> 01:18:32.320
Who is there?

01:18:33.520 --> 01:18:34.800
Mr. Rochester said,

01:18:36.560 --> 01:18:38.000
Don't you know me, Edward?

01:18:38.640 --> 01:18:39.280
I asked.

01:18:40.240 --> 01:18:41.440
Your dog knows me.

01:18:42.960 --> 01:18:44.720
I put the candles on a table.

01:18:45.680 --> 01:18:47.680
I held Mr. Rochester's hand.

01:18:49.520 --> 01:18:53.680
I know that voice and I know this little hand.

01:18:54.640 --> 01:18:55.920
Mr. Rochester said,

01:18:57.280 --> 01:18:58.080
Is that you,

01:18:58.800 --> 01:18:59.200
Jane?

01:19:00.480 --> 01:19:01.040
Yes, sir.

01:19:01.680 --> 01:19:03.440
I have found you at last.

01:19:04.080 --> 01:19:04.640
I said,

01:19:05.440 --> 01:19:07.280
I will never leave you again.

01:19:08.960 --> 01:19:11.920
Then I told Mr. Rochester my story.

01:19:14.080 --> 01:19:16.000
Why did you leave your cousins, Jane?

01:19:16.880 --> 01:19:18.160
Mr. Rochester asked,

01:19:19.360 --> 01:19:20.880
Why did you come back to me?

01:19:22.160 --> 01:19:23.120
I am blind.

01:19:23.840 --> 01:19:25.120
I have only one hand.

01:19:26.800 --> 01:19:28.560
I will take care of you, Edward.

01:19:29.280 --> 01:19:29.760
I said,

01:19:31.360 --> 01:19:32.960
But I don't want a servant.

01:19:33.760 --> 01:19:35.120
Mr. Rochester replied,

01:19:36.160 --> 01:19:37.120
I want a wife.

01:19:39.040 --> 01:19:40.720
You will have a wife, Edward.

01:19:41.280 --> 01:19:41.840
I said,

01:19:42.800 --> 01:19:44.000
I will be your wife.

01:19:45.040 --> 01:19:46.240
I will marry you.

01:19:47.200 --> 01:19:49.920
I loved you very much at Thornfield Hall.

01:19:50.720 --> 01:19:51.520
Now,

01:19:52.480 --> 01:19:53.600
I love you more.

01:19:55.920 --> 01:19:58.160
Mr. Rochester and I got married.

01:19:59.760 --> 01:20:00.560
After a time,

01:20:01.120 --> 01:20:02.320
his eyes were better.

01:20:03.440 --> 01:20:04.560
He could see a little.

01:20:06.080 --> 01:20:08.640
He saw the face of our first child.

01:20:10.560 --> 01:20:12.160
My dear Edward and I

01:20:13.040 --> 01:20:14.240
are very happy.

